name: python-engineio
raw_recipe:
{%set name = "python-engineio" %}
{%set version = "1.5.2" %}
{%set compress_type = "tar.gz" %}
{%set hash_type = "sha256" %}
{%set hash = "f70e874cda164f42c465e478afe1dd5b3de46f35b4818fbc3a6c7524c78ffe62" %}
{%set build = 0 %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.{{ compress_type }}
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.{{ compress_type }}
  {{ hash_type }}: {{ hash }}

build:
  number: {{ build }}
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record=record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools
    - six >=1.9.0

  run:
    - python
    - six >=1.9.0

test:
  imports:
    - engineio
    # - engineio.async_eventlet
    # - engineio.async_gevent
    # - engineio.async_gevent_uwsgi
    - engineio.async_threading
    - engineio.middleware
    - engineio.packet
    - engineio.payload
    - engineio.server
    - engineio.socket

about:
  home: https://github.com/miguelgrinberg/python-engineio/
  license_file: LICENSE
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  summary: 'Engine.IO server'
  doc_url: https://python-engineio.readthedocs.io
  dev_url: https://github.com/miguelgrinberg/python-engineio/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - pmlandwehr
